Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{600%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}, then
toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, remove all the packaging from the pork and add @Irish Pulled Pork{300%grams}
to an #oven dish{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and season with @BBQ Rub{2%sachet}.

Cover with #foil{} and cook on the middle shelf of the oven for ~{25-30%minutes}.

Once cooked, pull apart with the help of two #forks{} and stir through the
@BBQ Sauce{2%sachet}. IMPORTANT: Ensure the pork is piping hot throughout.

Finely chop the @chives{5%grams}(chopped) (use #scissors{} if easier).

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @creme fraiche{110%grams} and half the chives. Season
with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Pop half chips onto your #serving plate{}, season with salt and top with half the
@grated cheese{50%grams}, then half the pulled pork.

Repeat with the remaining chips, pork and cheese.

Drizzle over the creme fraiche and sprinkle over the remaining chives.